General.Name: Mineral Commodities Ltd
General.Description: Mineral Commodities Ltd, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the exploration, development, and evaluation of mineral deposits. It produces zircon, rutile, garnet, and ilmenite concentrates. The company is also involved in graphite mining and processing activities. In addition, it holds interests in the Tormin mineral sands project located in the Western Cape Province of South Africa; Skaland graphite operation located in the northern Norway on the island of Senja; and Munglinup graphite project located in the Great Southern region of Western Australia. The company was incorporated in 1970 and is headquartered in Belmont, Australia.
